Definition 2.2. Let ${\mathcal{C}}$ and ${\mathcal{D}}$ be dagger tensor categories. A dagger tensor functor $F:{\mathcal{C}}\to{\mathcal{D}}$ is a dagger functor equipped with a unitary natural transformation $\mu_{x,y}:F(x)\otimes F(y)\to F(x\otimes y)$ and a unitary isomorphism $i:1_{\mathcal{D}}\to F(1_{\mathcal{C}})$ such that the following identities hold for all $x,y,z\in{\mathcal{C}}$: $\displaystyle\mu_{x,y\otimes z}\circ(\operatorname{id}_{F(x)}\otimes\mu_{y,z})% =\mu_{x\otimes y,z}\circ(\mu_{x,y}\otimes\operatorname{id}_{F(z)})$ $\displaystyle\mu_{1,x}\circ(i\otimes\operatorname{id}_{F(x)})=\operatorname{id% }_{F(x)}\qquad\,\,\,\mu_{x,1}\circ(\operatorname{id}_{F(x)}\otimes i)=% \operatorname{id}_{F(x)}.$
Definition 2.7. A unitary fusion category is a dagger tensor category whose underlying dagger category is a C*-category, and whose underlying tensor category is a fusion category.
