Definition 2.16. We denote by $\widehat{\left(\mspace{3.0mu }\cdot\mspace{3.0mu }\right)}$ the composite $\mathcal{S}\stackrel{{\scriptstyle j}}{{\hookrightarrow}}\operatorname{Pro}% \left(\mathcal{S}\right)\stackrel{{\scriptstyle i^{*}}}{{\longrightarrow}}% \operatorname{Prof}\left(\mathcal{S}\right)$ and call it the profinite completion functor. Concretely, if $X$ is a space in $\mathcal{S},$ then $\widehat{X}$ corresponds to the composite $\mathcal{S}^{fc}\stackrel{{\scriptstyle i}}{{\hookrightarrow}}\mathcal{S}% \stackrel{{\scriptstyle\mathrm{Hom}\left(X,\mspace{3.0mu }\cdot\mspace{3.0mu }% \right)}}{{-\!\!\!-\!\!\!-\!\!\!-\!\!\!-\!\!\!-\!\!\!-\!\!\!-\!\!\!-\!\!\!-\!% \!\!-\!\!\!-\!\!\!\longrightarrow}}\mathcal{S}.$ This functor has a right adjoint given by the composite $\operatorname{Prof}\left(\mathcal{S}\right)\stackrel{{\scriptstyle% \operatorname{Pro}\left(i\right)}}{{\lhook\joinrel\relbar\joinrel\relbar% \joinrel\rightarrow}}\operatorname{Pro}\left(\mathcal{S}\right)\stackrel{{% \scriptstyle T}}{{\longrightarrow}}\mathcal{S}.$ We will denote this right adjoint simply by $U$.
